1.title: Film Lab Presents a Guest in My Own Country
1.plot: At one time or another, everyone has felt alone - like the only person in the room with long hair or brown skin or braces or a stutter or you name it. Here, Jennifer Betit Yen guides the viewer through several different takes on what it means to feel like the only person like you. . .as though you are a guest in the very place in which you live. Is there a universal place we can all call home, regardless of our race, ethnicity or religion?

3.title: Film Lab Presents Experiences in a New World
3.plot: We all want changes right? We want more jobs, better housing, healthier foods, greener communities. That kind of change starts with action and that action starts with us. As Herbert Read said, to realize that new world we must prefer the values of freedom and equality above all other values. Most importantly, we all have take action to make changes we want to happen, happen. It's a brave new world and this episode is all about the experience of living in it! Special thanks to Floating Heads, Kid Panda, Dorothy Xiao, Matthew Mui, Evan Kodani, Cinnabon Robots, Twelve ...

4.title: Family and Children, Sponsored by MyJennyBook
4.plot: In this special show devoted to family, Film Lab and MyJennyBook take viewers on an exploration of childhood, growing up and being part of a family.

5.title: Film Lab Presents Define Me
5.plot: What does it mean to be a minority member of a society, whether black or Latino or Asian or mixed race? This week's episode takes a closer look at some more stories that dare to "define me!"

6.title: Film Lab Presents Finding Your Place
6.plot: The great philosopher Aristotle said that knowing yourself is the beginning of all wisdom and Lewis Carrol, author of Alice in Wonderland, said "Who in the world am I? Ah, that's the great puzzle." However you look at it, we all go through a journey of self discovery and self definition as we try to find our places in this sometimes crazy-seeming world. Host Jennifer Betit Yen leads us through a series of vignettes exploring the theme of finding one's place, ranging from the serious meanderings in the mind of an artist in "The Illustrator" to a somewhat comical look ...

7.title: Film Lab Presents Kicking It Old School! A Made for AAFL TV Movie
7.plot: Drake and Vix are the top assassins of opposing crime organizations. Now they've been assigned to kill each other but... Meet two assassins that are both so good at what they do, they can't defeat each other. It's a story of rivals and their relationship, of rejecting roles to find peace, of finding that your worst enemy may be your best friend.

8.title: Film Lab Presents Ready? Set... ACTION!
8.plot: Ready for an action filled experience in the big city of NEW YORK!? Jennifer Betit Yen guides you through a series of adventures chock-filled with action and featuring all sorts of heroes, from the ones you might expect to the ones you just might not! Also featured in this episode: Jeryl Prescott (who can also be seen in season 1 of Walking Dead and on Modern Family). Special thanks: Kevin Lee, Toy Lei, Blue Core Studios, Eddie LeBron, SoCal Guerrillas, Barkada Inc., The Sexiest of the Bunch.

9.title: Film Lab Presents Falling in Love
9.plot: It's the season of love! Everyone finds the one in different ways. Some may be expected, some may be totally out of the blue and this episode of FILM LAB PRESENTS will take you on an exploration of nearly all of them. Special kudos to Pain N Love, The Dream Maker Crew, Team Fluffy Bunny, April Joy Limayo, Eddie Lebron, Fight for Love Game Show, A Green Bowl, Jennifer Betit Yen, Toy Lei, AAFL TV, Kyra Dacosta, Darren Bailey, and James Hutchison.

10.title: Film Lab Presents Romance in the City
10.plot: New York City has it all from the bright lights of Broadway to the exotic cuisine of Restaurant Row and what better place than New York is there in which to fall in love? In this episode, Film Lab takes you on a journey of several different characters who all find romance in the city. Special thanks to AAFL TV, Jennifer Betit Yen, Migina Tsai, Sunhoo Lee, Team Lee Kim, Eddie Shieh, Girard Tecson, James Shih, RiLL Films, Distance, Christian Oh, Candidate, Oz Productions.

11.title: Film Lab Presents Growing Up in the City
11.plot: Growing up isn't always easy. In fact, sometimes it can be downright difficult! In this episode, Film Lab explores self discovery. From learning about yourself through the help of others to recapturing a childhood long gone, people grow and learn from each lesson and memory of life.

12.title: Film Lab Presents a Made for AAFL TV Movie La La Land the Re Boot
12.plot: What happens when you mix a neurotic Type A attorney from New York with a detox obsessed pin up model from Los Angeles?

1.title: Film Lab Presents the Things We Do for Approval
1.plot: A series of "Film Lab Mash Ups" ranging from comedy to drama examining the issue of being a minority member of society through positive, non-academic, easily accessible, and creative original stories.

2.title: The Mistakes of Society
2.plot: Mistakes can happen in our society and those mistakes can affect us, our friends, our families, and even the people we don't know at all. From a funny stop motion animation to a more serious look at the issue, this show has it all.

3.title: Film Lab Presents Where Is the Line?
3.plot: A weekly showcase of deliciously diverse entertainment.

4.title: Film Lab Presents STILL
4.plot: In this special episode devoted to dance, STILL provides a beautiful performance piece directed and choreographed by William Lu and brought to us courtesy of the AOF Film Festival and AAFL TV, all about longing, love, loss, and connection - expressed through motion. With gratitude to Scott Eriksson and the Asians on Film Festival, AAFL TV and the Asian American Film Lab.

5.title: Film Lab Presents Epiphanies
5.plot: Diverse New Yorkers struggle with daily racial stereotypes that can be a part of everyday life anywhere in the world.

6.title: Film Lab Presents Avoid the Fangs
6.plot: An interplanetary chef shares her secrets for conquering a deadly recipe and a mysterious guest wreaks havoc in a posh boutique hotel, where the new guest services manager must risk her life to protect the guest's secret and protect the hotel's reputation.

7.title: Those That Matter
7.plot: Film Lab Presents a journey from a couple trying to salvage their romantic relationship to a sordid look inside the illegal world of human trafficking. Special guest directors Ryan Hayward, Steven Krimmel, and Eddie Lee. Special thanks to Max Turner, Jennifer Betit Yen, AAFL TV, Peyton Worley, The Jubilee Project, Scott Eriksson, AAFL TV, and AOF Film Festival.

8.title: Film Lab Presents Relativity
8.plot: Hayden and the Li family are put to the test with a matter that concerns them all...leaving everyone to question as a family, how relative is their connection? Directed by Ryan Hayward and Davis Noir. Starring Allen Theosky Rowe, Jesse Wang, Lee Chen, Sheena Chou. Andrew Abbott, and Jennifer Betit Yen.

9.title: Film Lab Presents Parents
9.plot: You love them. You hate them. You may have an up and down relationship with them, but you wouldn't be here without them. An exploration of parenthood. Special guest directors Will Kim, Rodney To and Fan He, with guest stars Xiangliang Kong, Paolo Montalban, Tina Chilip, Crystal Chiu, and Xinyu Liu. Includes special selections "Red Fog" and "Two Weeks," as well as the 4th episode of the bi-weekly comedy series MY NOT SO subCONSCIOUS, starring Jennifer Betit Yen and Kamran Kahn.

10.title: Film Lab Presents Women in Entertainment
10.plot: Special guest host Kelvin Han Yee takes us live to the red carpet in Hollywood to interview three actresses who took matters into their own hands by directing (Kelley Lund Portier), producing (Jennifer Betit Yen) and writing (Elizabeth Sung).

11.title: The Unexpected
11.plot: FILM LAB PRESENTS what happens when the unexpected occurs in people's love lives, from terrible wedding proposals to traveling photographers to unexpected encounters on the train. Special guest directors Amos Ezra Katz and Kamran Khan and guest stars Jennifer Betit Yen, Andy Baldeschwiler, Ray Gunn, Jim Chu, and Katherine Kine.

12.title: Deciding to Live
12.plot: People's lives are irrevocably changed and they must decide if and how to cope with those changes. With special guest directors Tuyen Do and Yuta Okamura.

13.title: All Things Must End
13.plot: In the finale of My Not So subConscious, Dani weeps over her failed marriage proposal with her friend Nisha. Nisha, who has some ulterior motives of her own, does NOT want to be friend zoned! Then, in an emotional vignette, we find out what happens when a frog, a seamstress and a factory king collide in Chinatown.

1.title: Refund
1.plot: Kicking off Season III is the episode entitled 'Refund,' which examines the difficulties of getting your money back. Watch what happens when roommates order take out and get themselves into a hairy situation. Then, travel to the distant future where earth memories are purchased in Memory 317 and family member's lives can be restored with a bit of DNA in Return. Finally, the first installment of the fabulously funny series La La Land! The series follows Jessica, a lawyer who decides to pack up and move to Los Angeles to pursue her dreams of acting after being fired ...

2.title: Loyalty
2.plot: What is the cost of keeping secrets? Desire and betrayal will test relationships, friendships and families. This episode features three of the 72 Hour Shootout Films: Himitsu, The Split End & The Necklace. Also featuring up and coming Filmmaker Darshon Crudup's Dilemma, which examines the NYPD's controversial stop and frisk policy through the eyes of a naive young woman.

3.title: It's Complicated
3.plot: In the golden age of Facebook and online dating, these filmmakers explore how to maintain a healthy relationship status... Or not. Featuring: Dyed, Tastes Like Teriyaki Chicken, Five Years & Breakfast. In Episode 2 of LaLa Land, Jessica struggles to find and stable relationship slash apartment with her roommate, Bunny. It's complicated!

4.title: Trapped
4.plot: A dead end 9 to 5 job, terminal illness, bullies, and "grey" hair... #TheStruggle. Featuring the following 72 Hour Shootout stories: Chasing the Startup Glory, Thick Skin, Fiery, He Got Grey and Rainbow Beautiful. Includes work by filmmakers Ryan Hayward, Jennifer Betit Yen, Blake Tamaki, Migina Tsai, Burak Tatar, Nicholas Molinari, Andrew Cheng, and Hung Vu.

5.title: A Variety Show
5.plot: A dating show, a reality show, a competition, and web series. Featuring: Case File 69, Underneath The Grey & America's Top Hairball. In Episode 3 of LaLa Land, Jessica and Bunny sign a lease and face a tough decision at dinner when Tammy and Justin order the entire menu and want to split the bill four ways.

6.title: No Pressure
6.plot: Anytime someone prefaces a sentence with "No pressure, but..." they are implying the impending pressure. Add stress into the equation when it's a family affair.

7.title: Baggage
7.plot: People hold things in. Sometimes they carry it around... Or explode... Or pack it up and deliver it you to in a coffee shop. This episode is dedicated to and dominated by female filmmakers.

8.title: Vows
8.plot: Let's stay together... Featuring: Lady In Waiting, Family Matters & The Revisit. Plus, in Episode 5 of LaLa Land, things get ... furry.

9.title: Obsessed
9.plot: Obsession can be deadly - Inside and out. Featuring: Untouched, Secret Asian Man, Imperfect, and The Color of My Heir.

10.title: Date Night
10.plot: Grab your loved one and a snuggie for Date Night! This episode features 72 Hour Shootout Films Special DelivRy, Family Portrait, Short (A Silent Film), and Accidentally Maybe, as well as the sixth and final installment of LaLa Land. Jessica's big break... maybe...

11.title: And the Winners Are
11.plot: The theme of the Film Lab's 2014 72 Hour Shootout was: The Color of my Hair. AsAm Film Lab has chosen to feature the best of the best filmmaker's short films to feature in their Season III Finale Episode.

1.title: The Bang Up
1.plot: A bang up of wild and zany sitcom style comedy rocks the worlds of a series of people, who at first glance may seem unrelated.

2.title: Shootout Spectacular
2.plot: In part two of this Shootout Spectacular, things get wild!

3.title: Your Voice Is Loud
3.plot: Racially sensitive issues come to the fore in a series of groups of people.

8.title: Film Lab Presents Focus on the Philippines Part 1
8.plot: Animated stories about a small town in the Philippines. The stories tell about daily life, friendship, World War II, hopes and dreams, individual victory over adverse circumstances, and collective celebration. Taken as a whole, these stories provide an impression of a Philippine community seen through a filter of memory and imagination.

9.title: Film Lab Presents Philippines Independence Day
9.plot: A special FILM LAB PRESENTS, the TV show, Focus on the Philippines, in honor of the Philippines Independence Day!

1.title: Film Lab Presents Matud Nila 1
1.plot: In this special Monday night "Focus on the Philippines" series, Film Lab Presents a short animated creation by John Day of a series of events and stories about a small rural town in the Philippines! Edited by Jason Wong! About creator John Day: As a digital media artist, John is interested in animated narratives that deal with memory. He combines various techniques and materials to develop imagery, including animated collage, mixed media drawing, altered photographs, text and miniature sets. He uses voice-over storytelling, sound effects and music in the sound tracks....
